# BLE Mesh Smart Onion Storage System on STM32WB55RG — Explained with the 6W Method

A BLE Mesh–based smart onion storage system is an intelligent warehouse/storage monitoring network where multiple wireless sensor nodes continuously monitor onion storage conditions and cooperate using Bluetooth Low Energy (BLE) Mesh networking.

The STMicroelectronics STM32WB55RG is especially suitable because it combines:

* An ARM Cortex-M4 application core
* A Cortex-M0+ wireless core
* Integrated Bluetooth 5 / BLE Mesh support
* Ultra-low power operation
* Real-time sensing capability

This makes it ideal for distributed agricultural storage monitoring.

---

# 1. WHAT is the Project?

## Core Idea

The project is a **distributed smart onion storage monitoring and control system** using BLE Mesh.

Instead of one centralized controller with many wires:

* Multiple wireless sensor nodes are placed across onion storage racks.
* Every node measures environmental conditions.
* Nodes communicate through BLE Mesh.
* Data is forwarded hop-by-hop to a gateway.
* The gateway sends data to:

  * Mobile app
  * Cloud dashboard
  * Local control system

The system helps reduce:

* Onion rotting
* Fungal growth
* Moisture accumulation
* Sprouting
* Weight loss
* Storage inefficiency

---

# Problem in Traditional Onion Storage

Onions are highly sensitive to:

* Humidity
* Temperature
* Air circulation
* Ethylene accumulation
* Water condensation

Traditional storage problems:

| Problem                | Effect                |
| ---------------------- | --------------------- |
| High humidity          | Rotting               |
| Poor airflow           | Fungal infection      |
| Temperature variation  | Sprouting             |
| Manual monitoring      | Human error           |
| No distributed sensing | Hidden spoilage zones |

Large warehouses often lose 20–40% stock during long storage periods.

---

# Smart BLE Mesh Solution

The BLE Mesh network creates a distributed sensing system.

## Each Node Can Measure

* Temperature
* Humidity
* Gas concentration
* Airflow
* Light exposure
* Smoke/fire
* Door status

## Nodes Cooperate

If one node is far from the gateway:

Node A → Node B → Node C → Gateway

This is the key advantage of mesh networking.

